    <briefdescription>
<para>Timestamp callback handler struct. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Stores the timestamp callback information. Caller must make sure that the variable pointed by this is valid during the lifetime of registration. Typically this means that the variable cannot be allocated from stack. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
